          <h2><span>Our Story</span></h2>
          <div class="text-block">
            Steve and Caroline met while camping out as freshmen for NCSU/UNC basketball tickets during January of 2008. Steve told Caroline she wasn't very photogenic and Caroline told Steve that she hated him. It was less than love at first sight. Despite all this, they became very close friends. They were told about a thousand times what a cute couple they were, and they got really good at saying, "We're just friends." One night, Caroline invited Steve to go out for milkshakes. He was an hour late picking her up, which she later learned was because he was on the phone with his mom deciding if he should tell Caroline how he felt about her. They went on their first date on Valentine's Day of 2009 and everything became official. Three years went by, and they spent their time transitioning from being broke college kids to being a broke web developer and an even more broke teacher. They traveled to Washington DC, Atlantic City, California, and Charleston. They went to lots of concerts and lots of football games. They adopted a wild but adorable puppy named Russell (a la Russell Wilson). They got asked three times a week when they would get engaged but they took their time (much to Caroline's chagrin). Finally, on Caroline's 23rd birthday, Steve took her to a delicious dinner at The Pit, then blindfolded her and drove her back to the field where they first met and got down on one knee. Obviously, she said yes, or this website would be significantly more awkward.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
