  <div class="section the-big-day champagne" data-section-name="the-big-day">
    <div class="container">
      <h2><span>The Big Day</span></h2>
      <div class="text-block">
        If you know us, you know we don't take anything <strong>too</strong> seriously. We want our Wedding Day to be a time to celebrate with our friends and family, show our love for each other in front of everyone, and eat (and drink) a <strong>lot</strong>. The ceremony and the reception will both be held at <a href="http://thestockroomat230.com" target="_blank">The Stockroom</a> at 230 Fayetteville Street in Raleigh. Yay, convenience! The ceremony will start at <strong>5 pm sharp</strong> (provided Caroline is on time, which is unlikely). We're looking to get this thing done in the realm of 15 minutes. You're welcome. Cocktail hour will immediately follow the ceremony. Our lovely caterer has agreed to "flip" the room for us while we take pictures, which means you fine people will be having drinks and hors d'ouevres in the front part of The Stockroom. Feel free to mingle wherever you please, just know that the reception will be starting at 6:30. You can expect delicious food, flowing drinks, and questionable (but enthusiastic) dance moves. The show's over at 10 pm, but the great news is we'll be in Downtown Raleigh and we can continue the tomfoolery wherever we choose.
      </div>
